    <string name="about_credits_title">Credits &amp; Origins</string>
    <string name="about_credits_desc">This project is based on the excellent open-source project by Grégory D, with deep localization and feature enhancements. Sincere thanks to the original author for his outstanding contributions to the open-source voice community!</string>
    <string name="about_enhancement_title">Localization &amp; Enhancement Statement</string>
    <string name="about_enhancement_desc">This version features full-text deep localization by yuaxi, along with a comprehensive refactoring of system compatibility code to fix multiple underlying background crash issues. Meanwhile, targeting the scenario of always-on tactical voice comms on mobile, exclusive secondary development added core features such as the [Minimalist Translucent Always-on Floating Console], significantly optimizing the mic/mute interaction experience during esports and gaming.</string>
    <string name="about_license_title">Open Source License (GPLv3)</string>
    <string name="about_license_desc">This project strictly follows the GNU GPLv3 (GNU General Public License v3) open-source license. This means any individual or team modifying or deriving redistributions from this project MUST keep it completely open-source, unconditionally adopt the GPLv3 license, and fully retain the copyright attribution of the original author (Grégory D) and the secondary localization developer (yuaxi). Any form of closed-source packaging, secondary encryption, or secret profiteering is strictly prohibited!</string>
    <string name="about_repo_title">Official Source Repository &amp; Updates</string>
    <string name="about_repo_desc">The complete source code of this project, subsequent official feature iterations, experience optimizations, and emergency bug fix patches will be published first independently in my official GitHub repository. Welcome to Star, follow, report Issues, or submit PRs:</string>
    <string name="about_repo_link">🔗 Click to visit yuaxi\'s open-source GitHub repository</string>
    <string name="about_warning_title">⚠️ Anti-Fraud (Solemn Disclaimer)</string>
    <string name="about_warning_desc">This program is a purely public-welfare, non-profit product for open-source technical exchange. It is completely FREE and completely OPEN-SOURCE! Any form of commercial peddling, packaging buyout, or bundled key-code charging is strictly prohibited. If you obtained this software through paid channels (such as second-hand bots, trading platforms, paid downloading services, etc.), you have been scammed! Please immediately initiate a refund claim for infringement on the platform, and head to the official open-source repository to report the black-market scalpers with your real name!</string>
